Messaging Error Codes in Service Cloud

Identify errors encountered during WhatsApp, Facebook Messenger, Apple Messages for Business, and SMS messaging sessions.

Error codes are categorized by their starting number:

0xxx Errors
Error codes indicate a problem communicating with the third-party messaging provider or service carrier.
0001 Can't contact the messaging service right now. Try again later.
0002 Can't contact the messaging service right now. Try again later.
...
3015 Something’s wrong with this messaging component’s parameters.

1xxx Errors
Error codes indicate a problem with the source address.
1001 Can't send messages from this channel. Ask your admin to check the channel settings and contact Salesforce Customer Support.
1003 Can't send messages from this channel because the channel's phone number isn’t verified.
...
1004 Can’t send messages from this channel because the channel’s phone number is blocked.

2xxx Errors
Error codes indicate a problem with the destination address.
2001 Can't send messages to this number. Make sure that the contact information is correct and try again.
2002 Can't send messages to this recipient because they blocked you.
...
2004 Messages to this recipient are getting blocked by their carrier.

3xxx Errors
Error codes indicate a problem with the message being sent.
3001 Can't send this message because it contains invalid content. Try rewriting it.
...
3015 Something’s wrong with this messaging component’s parameters.

Other Errors
9999 Can’t send this message right now. If this happens again, ask your Salesforce admin to contact Salesforce Customer Support.
title: Messaging Error Codes in Service Cloud
